            <h1>The environment</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/Upload/PORTAL/Temabilder/miljo_150x113.jpg" alt="Woman in a field of yellow flowers" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">Norway aims to be a leading nation in terms of environmental policy. If future generations are to have access to a good environment and unspoiled nature, then adequate consideration must be given to the environment in everything we do. Norway must base its environmental policy on the principle of sustainable development, which includes demonstrating solidarity with coming generations, both in Norway and abroad. This means protecting essential environmental resources and ensuring fully adequate management of natural resources.</p>
            <img src="/Upload/PORTAL/Temabilder/miljo_150x113.jpg" alt="Woman in a field of yellow flowers" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p>It is the <em>Ministry of the Environment</em> that has chief responsibility for the Government’s environmental policy. Environmental policy cuts across ministerial boundaries and involves issues that are the responsibility of several different ministries. </p>
<p>On this page you will find general information and documents relating to the environment. You can explore this topic in more detail by using the menu on the right.</p></div>
